          "description": "The site site is located within the Metropolitan Green Belt. Permission was granted in 2006 (06/00672/DEEM3) for the main school to provide urgent specialist teaching facilities. \n\nThe new buildings will be built adjacent the existing school on an unused grass area which occupied approximately 118m2 of space. The 2x new classrooms are approximately 75m2 in total with the remaining area being hardstanding between the new buildings which will act as an outdoor teaching space for students to practice bricklaying and other vocational skills and techniques. \n\nThe building location is in-keeping with the adjacent school and do not affect the character of the significant greenbelt site which is approx 32,000m2. The proposed site area uses a largely unused grassed area adjacent the car park, no access to the main playing field areas are affected. No trees or hedgerows are affected by the proposals. \n\nAccess to the school site is restricted for safeguarding purposes. \n\nThe proposed change of use is open space to teaching space. ",
